# HERMES UI Conventions

## Theme
- Dark background: `bg-[#08080C]` (main), `bg-[#0A0A10]` (header/footer)
- Borders: `border-white/5`
- Text: white with opacity levels (`text-white/40`, `text-white/30`)
- Accent: violet/purple gradient (`from-violet-600 to-blue-600`)
- Bullish: emerald/green tones (light, not too dark)
- Bearish: red/orange tones (light, not too dark)

## Module Structure
Each module has its own component in `src/components/modules/`:
- `Module200Week.tsx` - uses `useScanContext()`
- `Module200Day.tsx` - uses `useScan200DContext()`
- New modules should follow the same pattern with their own context

## Layout Pattern
- `Layout.tsx` owns all global state via dual React Context
- Modules receive state via context hooks, not props
- Header shows: market status indicator, auto-refresh toggle, last refresh time, scan button
- Module navigation tabs in header

## Language
- UI labels are in Turkish (Tara, Seans Acik, Kapanisa, etc.)
- Code comments can be Turkish or English
